Operatives of Imo Police Command have repelled an unknown gunmen attack on Ideato South Local Government Area Police station. The Command’s Public Relations Officer, Michael Abattam who disclosed this said the attack, which occurred at about 0230 hours, at Ideato South Police Station, involved some unknown gunmen who came in their numbers, shooting sporadically, throwing Improvised Explosive Devices (IEDs) into the station. He said, “the hoodlums were immediately repelled by the Command’s tactical teams and the police operatives of the division. And in the ensuing gun duel, the hoodlums were overwhelmed by the superior fire-power of the police, resulting in several of them fleeing into the bush with various degrees of bullet injuries. Nasarawa Earmarks 2.23bn For Rural  Electrification Emir Of Borgu Inaugurates Committee On Gani Durbar Festival “No life or arms was lost and the detonated Improvised Explosive Devices (IEDs) only caused minimal damage,’’ he added.